[[File:AssaultConcussionMissiles-SWArmada.png|thumb|right|300px|A ''Victory''-class Star Destroyer launching assault concussion missiles.]]
The '''assault concussion missile''' was a capital ship grade [[Concussion missile/Legends|concussion missile]] in use by [[Capital ship/Legends|capital ships]].

Exponentially more powerful than smaller versions commonly used on [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighters]], these heavy missiles were primarily used for [[Orbital bombardment/Legends|planetary bombardment]] and anti-capital ship duty, and were typically carried aboard heavier [[Warship/Legends|warships]] such as [[Star Destroyer/Legends|Star Destroyers]] like the [[Victory I-class Star Destroyer/Legends|''Victory I''-class]], [[Gladiator-class Star Destroyer/Legends|''Gladiator''-class]] and [[Nebula-class Star Destroyer|''Nebula''-class Star Destroyer]], and [[Battleship/Legends|battleships]] like the [[Executor-class Star Dreadnought/Legends|''Executor''-class Star Dreadnought]] and [[Viscount-class Star Defender|''Viscount''-class Star Defender]]. Also [[Battlecruiser/Legends|battlecruisers]] like the [[Maelstrom-class battle cruiser/Legends|''Maelstrom''-class]], [[Heavy cruiser/Legends|heavy cruisers]] like the [[Acclamator-class transgalactic military assault ship/Legends|''Acclamator''-class]].

A standard assault concussion missile could severely damage a capital ship, with rarely more than a handful being needed to destroy a target completely. Some assault concussion missiles were equipped with enormously heavy [[Chepatite impact explosive|Chepatite]]-[[Thorium/Legends|Thorium]] warheads encased in a [[Durasteel/Legends|durasteel]] penatrator, enabling the missiles to pierce through layers of soil, stone, armor, and [[Duralloy/Legends|duralloy]] to detonate deep within a target.<ref name="Lead by Example">''[[Lead by Example]]''</ref>

